erect /ɪˈrɛkt/

(erecting,erected,erects) 

1. V-T If people erect something such as a building, bridge, or barrier, they build it or create it. 建造 [正式] 

例： Opposition demonstrators have erected barricades in roads leading to the parliament building. 反对派示威者在通往议会大厦的路上设置了路障。 

